ragarh Fort]]\n* [[Maham#Maham Fort|Maham Fort]]\n* [[Nahar Singh Mahal]]\n* [[Pijore Fort]]\n* [[Raipur Rani Fort]]\n* [[Saduara Fort]]\n* [[Sirsa Fort]] in [[Sirsa]]<ref name=\"Hiltebeitel Hiltebeitel 1999 p. 174\">{{cite book | last=Hiltebeitel | first=P.R.A. | last2=Hiltebeitel | first2=A. | title=Rethinking India's Oral and Classical Epics: Draupadi Among Rajputs, Muslims, and Dalits | publisher=University of Chicago Press | year=1999 | isbn=978-0-226-34050-0 | url=https://books.google.dk/books?id=uV-RrRoMzbgC&pg=PA174 | access-date=20 October 2018 | page=174}}</ref>\n* [[Tosham Fort]]\n* [[Thaneshvar Fort]]\n{{Div col end}}\n\n== Himachal Pradesh ==\n* [[Arki Fort]]\n* [[Beja Palace]]\n* [[Jaitak Fort]]\n* [[Kahlur Fort]]\n* [[Kamlah Fort]]\n* [[Kangra Fort]]\n* [[Kunihar Fort]]\n* [[Kutlehar Fort]]\n* [[Mahlog Fort]]\n* [[Nadaun Fort, Hamirpur]]\n\n== Jammu and Kashmir ==\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n* [[Akhnoor Fort]]\n* [[Bahu Fort]]\n* [[Bhimgarh Fort]]\n* [[Chiktan Fort]]\n* [[Hari Parbat Fort]]\n* [[Jasmergarh Fort]]\n* [[Ramnagar Fort Udhampur|Ramnagar Fort]]\n{{Div col end}}\n\n== Jharkhand ==\n* [[Palamu Fort]]\n* [[Shahpur Fort]]\n\n== Karnataka ==\n{{main list|List of forts in Karnataka}}\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n* [[Basavakalyana Fort]]\n* [[Bellary Fort]]\n* [[Bidar Fort]]\n* [[Bijapur Fort]]\n* [[Chitradurga Fort]]\n* [[Gulbarga Fort]]<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.hindu.com/2011/01/09/stories/2011010955200300.htm| title=Gulbarga fort to be restored| publisher=| accessdate=2013-04-18}}</ref>\n* [[Jamalabad]] Fort\n* [[Kittur Fort]]\n* [[Sakleshpur#Tourism|Manjarabad Fort]]\n* [[Mirjan Fort]]\n* [[Mudgal]] Fort\n* [[Raichur]] Fort\n* [[Savadatti Fort]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n== Kerala ==\n{{Div col|colwidth=30em}}\n* [[Anchuthengu Fort]]\n* [[Bekal Fort]]\n* [[Chandragiri Fort, Kerala|Chandragiri Fort]]\n* [[Cranganore Fort]] (also called Kodungallur Fort, Kottapuram Fort)\n* [[East Fort]]\n* [[Fort Emmanuel]]\n* [[Fort Thomas, Tangasseri|Fort Thomas]]\n* [[Hosdurg Fort]]\n* [[Nedumkotta]], a city wall\n* [[Palakkad Fort]]\n* [[Pallipuram Fort]]\n* [[St. Angelo Fort]] (also known as Kannur Fort or Kannur Kotta)\n* [[Tellicherry Fort]]\n* [[William Fort]] (also called Chettuva Fort)\n{{Div col end}}\n\n== Madhya Pradesh ==\n\n* Ater fort[[Bhind district|Bh]]\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n* [[Rewa Fort]]\n* [[Maheshwar|Ahilya Fort]]\n* [[Asirgarh Fort]]\n* [[Bajrangarh Fort]]\n* [[Bandhavgarh Fort]]\n* [[Chanderi fort]]\n* [[Ginnorgarh fort]]\n* [[Datia Palace|Datia Fort]]\n* [[Dhar Fort]]\n* [[Garh Kundar]]\n* [[Gadpahra]]\n* [[Gohad Fort]]\n* [[Gwalior Fort]]\n* [[Garrauli State|Garrauli Fort]]\n* [[Hinglajgarh]]\n* [[Kamakandla Fort]]\n* [[Madan Mahal, Jabalpur|Madan Mahal]]\n* [[Mandsaur Fort]]\n* [[Mandu, Madhya Pradesh|Mandu fort complex]]\n* [[Narwar Fort]]\n* [[Orchha Fort complex]]\n* [[Raisen]] fort\n* [[Rampayli fort]]\n* [[Sabalgarh Fort]]\n* [[Sheopur]]\n* [[Sendhwa]]\n* [[Vijayraghavgarh]]\n* [[Utila Fort]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n== Maharashtra ==\n{{See also|List of forts in Mumbai|Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj}}\n{{div col|colwidth=16em}}\n# [[Achala Fort]]\n# [[Agashi Fort]]\n# [[Ahmednagar Fort]]\n# [[Ahme]]\n# [[Ahivant Fort]]\n#[[Ajinkyatara]]\n# [[Akola Fort]]\n# [[Akluj Fort]]\n# [[Alang Fort]]\n# [[Ambolgad]]\n# [[Anjaneri]]\n# [[Anjanvel Fort]]\n# [[Ankai Fort]]\n# [[Antur Fort]]\n# [[Arnala fort]]\n# [[Asheri fort]]\n# [[Asava fort]]\n# [[Avchitgad]]\n# [[Avandha Fort]]\n# [[Balapur Fort]]\n# [[Ballarpur Fort]]\n# [[Bankot fort]]\n# [[Bahadur Fort]]\n# [[Belapur Fort]]\n# [[Bhagwantgad]]\n# [[Bhairavgad]]\n# [[Bhamer Dhule]]\n# [[Bharatgad]]\n# [[Bhaskargad]]/[[Basgad]]\n# [[Bhavangad Fort]]/Bhondgad\n# [[Bhorgiri fort]]\n# [[Bhudargad]] Fort\n# [[Bhupatgad Fort]]\n# [[Bhushangad]]\n# [[Birwadi fort]]\n# [[Bitangad]]\n# [[Bombay Castle]]\n# [[Castella de Aguada]]\n# [[Chanda Fort]]\n# [[Chandan Fort]]\n# [[Chanderi Fort]]\n# [[Chandragad]]/Dhavalgad\n# [[Chandwad fort]]\n# [[Chauler Fort]]/C